Actor Femi Adebayo has signed an endorsement deal to serve as an ambassador for paytv, StarTimes. The Nation reliably gathered that Adebayo was appointed the brand ambassador by digital-TV platform, StarTimes after several talks that began in 2021. On Monday, January 10, 2022, the actor and director was unveiled by StarTimes. Chief Executive Officer, StarTimes, Alex Jian said Adebayo is an actor who exhibits all that StarTimes, an affordable digital-TV platform, stands for. “StarTimes made digital-TV entertainment available to all homes and has continued to offer unmatched service delivery to every household, irrespective of income level. Adebayo is greatly loved by Nollywood fans. - Advertisement - “We are delighted to have Adebayo as our brand ambassador. Over the years, Femi has continued to add value to our TV screens. We are delighted with this partnership.   ‘We Rise: The Davido Story’ premieres on January 15     Portable, promoter in cryptic war of words     Golden Globes 2022: Will Smith, Nicole Kidman, Squid Game…   “We have decided to work with the veteran actor who also shares our core values in terms of dedication, service, and quality entertainment,” Jian said. Adebayo said: “StarTimes offers something tasty. It resonates with the kind of entertainment that Femi Adebayo always doles out. I am happy to represent the StarTimes brand.” The endorsement deal reinforces the business relationship between StarTimes and Adebayo in strengthening the investment in local content. Adebayo, who enjoys cult followership in the movie industry, engaged StarTimes to produce a Nollywood production entitled Ile-Alayo. The paytv also launched another comedy series, ‘Okirika,’ which is produced by Muka Ray.